    {
      "kind": "proposition",
      "label": "Sedrakyan's inequality",
      "anchor": {
        "section": "Sedrakyan's lemma – positive real numbers",
        "snippet": "Sedrakyan's inequality , also known as"
      },
      "status": "formalized",
      "mathlib": {
        "decl": "sq_sum_div_le_sum_sq_div",
        "module": "Mathlib.Algebra.Order.BigOperators.Ring.Finset",
        "match_kind": "exact"
      },
      "note": "`sq_sum_div_le_sum_sq_div` is documented as Sedrakyan's/Titu's/Engel's lemma: (∑fᵢ)²/∑gᵢ ≤ ∑ fᵢ²/gᵢ.",
      "provenance": "ai",
      "anchors": [
        {
          "section": "Sedrakyan's lemma – positive real numbers",
          "snippet": "Sedrakyan's inequality , also known as"
        },
        {
          "type": "math_alttext",
          "value": "{\\displaystyle {\\frac {\\left(u_{1}+u_{2}+\\cdots +u_{n}\\right)^{2}}{v_{1}+v_{2}+\\cdots +v_{n}}}\\leq {\\frac {u_{1}^{2}}{v_{1}}}+{\\frac {u_{2}^{2}}{v_{2}}}+\\cdots +{\\frac {u_{n}^{2}}{v_{n}}},}"
        },
        {
          "type": "math_alttext",
          "value": "{\\displaystyle {\\dfrac {\\left(\\sum \\limits _{i=1}^{n}u_{i}\\right)^{2}}{\\sum \\limits _{i=1}^{n}v_{i}}}\\leq \\sum _{i=1}^{n}{\\frac {u_{i}^{2}}{v_{i}}}.}"
        }
      ],
      "id": "cc0b8e71d715"
    },
    {
      "kind": "example",
      "label": "Cauchy–Schwarz in the plane R²",
      "anchor": {
        "section": "R 2 - The plane",
        "snippet": "then the Cauchy–Schwarz inequality becomes"
      },
      "status": "formalized",
      "mathlib": {
        "decl": "sum_mul_sq_le_sq_mul_sq",
        "module": "Mathlib.Algebra.Order.BigOperators.Ring.Finset",
        "match_kind": "generalization"
      },
      "note": "The R² dot-product case is the two-term instance of the general finite-sum Cauchy–Schwarz `sum_mul_sq_le_sq_mul_sq`.",
      "provenance": "ai",
      "anchors": [
        {
          "section": "R 2 - The plane",
          "snippet": "then the Cauchy–Schwarz inequality becomes"
        },
        {
          "type": "math_alttext",
          "value": "{\\displaystyle \\langle \\mathbf {u} ,\\mathbf {v} \\rangle ^{2}={\\bigl (}\\|\\mathbf {u} \\|\\|\\mathbf {v} \\|\\cos \\theta {\\bigr )}^{2}\\leq \\|\\mathbf {u} \\|^{2}\\|\\mathbf {v} \\|^{2},}"
        }
      ],
      "id": "e68fe1091fed"
    },
    {
      "kind": "example",
      "label": "Cauchy–Schwarz in Rⁿ",
      "anchor": {
        "section": "R n : n -dimensional Euclidean space",
        "snippet": "with the standard inner product, which is the dot product"
      },
      "status": "formalized",
      "mathlib": {
        "decl": "sum_mul_sq_le_sq_mul_sq",
        "module": "Mathlib.Algebra.Order.BigOperators.Ring.Finset",
        "match_kind": "exact"
      },
      "note": "`sum_mul_sq_le_sq_mul_sq` is exactly (∑fᵢgᵢ)² ≤ (∑fᵢ²)(∑gᵢ²), the Cauchy–Schwarz inequality for the dot product on Rⁿ.",
      "provenance": "ai",
      "anchors": [
        {
          "section": "R n : n -dimensional Euclidean space",
          "snippet": "with the standard inner product, which is the dot product"
        },
        {
          "type": "math_alttext",
          "value": "{\\displaystyle {\\biggl (}\\sum _{i=1}^{n}u_{i}v_{i}{\\biggr )}^{2}\\leq {\\biggl (}\\sum _{i=1}^{n}u_{i}^{2}{\\biggr )}{\\biggl (}\\sum _{i=1}^{n}v_{i}^{2}{\\biggr )}.}"
        }
      ],
      "id": "ae08abc6b425"
    },
    {
      "kind": "example",
      "label": "Cauchy–Schwarz in Cⁿ",
      "anchor": {
        "section": "C n : n -dimensional complex space",
        "snippet": "is the canonical complex inner product"
      },
      "status": "formalized",
      "mathlib": {
        "decl": "inner_mul_inner_self_le",
        "module": "Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Basic",
        "match_kind": "generalization"
      },
      "note": "Cⁿ with its canonical inner product is an RCLike inner product space, so the general `inner_mul_inner_self_le` specializes to this case.",
      "provenance": "ai",
      "anchors": [
        {
          "section": "C n : n -dimensional complex space",
          "snippet": "is the canonical complex inner product"
        },
        {
          "type": "math_alttext",
          "value": "{\\displaystyle {\\bigl |}\\langle \\mathbf {u} ,\\mathbf {v} \\rangle {\\bigr |}^{2}={\\Biggl |}\\sum _{k=1}^{n}u_{k}{\\bar {v}}_{k}{\\Biggr |}^{2}\\leq \\langle \\mathbf {u} ,\\mathbf {u} \\rangle \\langle \\mathbf {v} ,\\mathbf {v} \\rangle ={\\biggl (}\\sum _{k=1}^{n}u_{k}{\\bar {u}}_{k}{\\biggr )}{\\biggl (}\\sum _{k=1}^{n}v_{k}{\\bar {v}}_{k}{\\biggr )}=\\sum _{j=1}^{n}|u_{j}|^{2}\\sum _{k=1}^{n}|v_{k}|^{2}.}"
        }
      ],
      "id": "f267b0891777"
    },
    {
      "kind": "example",
      "label": "Cauchy–Schwarz in L²",
      "anchor": {
        "section": "L 2",
        "snippet": "For the inner product space of square-integrable complex-valued functions"
      },
      "status": "formalized",
      "mathlib": {
