        "module": "Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.Basic",
        "match_kind": "generalization"
      },
      "note": "L² is given an inner product space instance (Mathlib.MeasureTheory.Function.L2Space), so the general `norm_inner_le_norm` yields the L² Cauchy–Schwarz inequality.",
      "provenance": "ai",
      "anchors": [
        {
          "section": "L 2",
          "snippet": "For the inner product space of square-integrable complex-valued functions"
        },
        {
          "type": "math_alttext",
          "value": "{\\displaystyle \\left|\\int _{\\mathbb {R} ^{n}}f(x){\\overline {g(x)}}\\,dx\\right|^{2}\\leq \\int _{\\mathbb {R} ^{n}}{\\bigl |}f(x){\\bigr |}^{2}\\,dx\\int _{\\mathbb {R} ^{n}}{\\bigl |}g(x){\\bigr |}^{2}\\,dx.}"
        }
      ],
      "id": "32c7d03e253c"
